<h1>BraDyCMS template system docs</h1>

<p>BraDyCMS uses <a href="http://twig.sensiolabs.org/" target="_blank">Twig</a> for templating web sites.</p>
<p>Please refer to <a href="http://twig.sensiolabs.org/doc/templates.html" target="_blank">the official documenttation</a> for Twig usage.</p>
<p>Template file, located in <code>./sites/default/</code> folder receives one argument named <code>html</code>, instance of object <code>OutHtml</code>. It's available methods, and usage is documented beneath</p>
<p>For a fully working template example follow <a href="#docs/tmpl/example">this link</a></p>

<h2>class OutHtml</h2>
<p class="lead">OutHtml extends class Out and inherits all it's public methods. As a general rule methods of class Out return PHP strings and arrays and methods of OutHtml return well formatted HTML code.</p>

<p>To call public methods (listed beneath) in template files (<code>*.twig</code>) just use the following syntax: <code>{% raw %} {{ html.methodName }} {% endraw %}</code></p>

<p>For example: <code>{% raw %}{{ html.getContext }}{% endraw %}</code> will return the actual context, i.e. one of the strings <code>home</code>, <code>article</code>, <code>tags</code> or <code>search</code>.</p>

